    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.124/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Treasury</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1724fn1">Mutatis mutandis, to the Secretary of War.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to recent correspondence on the
                    subject of an American sanitary expert for the sanitation of Iquitos, Peru, I
                    have the honor to inform you that the Legation at Lima telegraphs under date of
                    the 3d instant that the President of Peru confides in the good <pb facs="1398"
                        n="1282" xml:id="pg_1282"/> faith of any expert this Government might
                    recommend as to the duration and terms of his employment, and that he authorizes
                    the offer of a salary of seventy-five pounds sterling per month, or as much as
                    one hundred pounds. The Legation adds that if this offer should be considered
                    insufficient the President of Peru would consider a counter proposal.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
